accessibility.text: Literatuur enclosed in this learning path

Research results do not automatically translate into meaningful improvements in clinical practice. They need to be found by healthcare professionals, translated to the concrete context and implemented in daily practice. Now that you are experts in the first two steps (looking for evidence and translating it into practice), we want to introduce you to implementation sciences. It is a young science (sinds 2006) in full evolution, but there is no lack of theoretical insights. This learning path will introduce you to some important frameworks, and help you plan your next implementation project.
Topics: emergency nursing; prehospital care; patient safety; healthcare engineering
